HEADWORD: Bogle
<hw>Bo"gle</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot. and North Eng.
<ets>bogle</ets>, <ets>bogill</ets>, <ets>bugill</ets>, specter; as a
verb, to terrify, fr. W. <ets>bwgwl</ets> threatening, fear,
<ets>bwg</ets>, <ets>bwgan</ets>, specter, hobgoblin. Cf.
<er>Bug</er>.]</ety> <def>A goblin; a specter; a frightful phantom; a
bogy; a bugbear.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>boggle</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bogota</ent>⟦br⟧
